# BVF Parser & Resolution Engine

This project implements the Behavioral Verification Framework (BVF) —
a spec language for TDD/BDD-style behavioral declarations that AI agents
use to drive implementation.

The system parses `.bvf` files, builds a dependency graph from `@{references}`,
tracks materialization state, and provides a CLI for managing specs.


#decl surface cli-tool
  A Node.js CLI application invoked as `bvf` from the command line.
  It reads `.bvf` files from the current directory (recursively)
  and maintains state in a `.bvf-state/` directory.

  The CLI is implemented in TypeScript, compiled to JavaScript,
  and can be run via `node` or as a standalone binary.

  For testing, invoke the CLI as `node dist/cli.js` or use
  the exported API functions directly in unit tests.
#end


#decl surface library-api
  The core BVF engine exposed as a TypeScript/JavaScript library.
  This is the programmatic API that the CLI wraps.

  Functions are imported from the main package entry point.
  All functions operate on in-memory data structures or
  file system paths passed as arguments.
#end

#end
